com.esri.mo2.map.draw
Class AoFillStyle

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.esri.mo2.map.draw.AoFillStyle
public class AoFillStyle
extends Object

Stores all the predefined fill style constants and provides the corresponding Paint object by calling the appropriate getPaint method. This is used by the various Polygon symbols to determine how to fill or paint the symbol.

Example of usage:


      SimplePolygonSymbol ps = new SimplePolygonSymbol();
      ps.setPaint(AoFillStyle.getPaint(AoFillStyle.GRAY_FILL, java.awt.Color.red));

getPaint

public static Paint getPaint(int style,
                             Color fillColor)
Returns the Paint object representing the specified FillStyle and FillColor.

If the style parameter is SOLID_FILL, the FillColor will be returned as is.

If the style parameter is TRANSPARENT_FILL, null is returned.

Parameters:
style - the FillStyle for the polygon symbol
fillColor - the FillColor for the polygon symbol
Returns:
a Paint object
